 As a risk-averse individual, I would prefer to minimize potential losses and maximize the chances of earning a consistent income. In this game, both choices seem to have an equal chance of leading to a higher reward for the opponent (R vs B), so there's no clear advantage in choosing one over the other based on that factor.

However, I would lean towards choosing R more often due to the larger potential payoff when my opponent chooses B (45$ compared to 40$). On the flip side, if my opponent consistently chooses R and I choose B, I will still earn a guaranteed 20$ every round. Over the course of 75 rounds, this strategy would yield a total of 1500$, whereas choosing R only 60 times (to match my opponent's R choices) would result in a total of 1350$. This difference of 150$ might not seem significant when considering the risk involved, but it still favors choosing B more often.

In conclusion, I will choose B as my primary choice and occasionally switch to R to maximize my chances of earning the larger payoff while minimizing potential losses. {B}
